Vice President Joe Biden has released a statement expressing his admiration for Avril Haines, who has been selected as the Deputy National Security Advisor. Biden has known Haines since she served as his counsel on the Foreign Relations Committee of the United States Senate, and he praises her intelligence and insight into national security challenges. Haines has a distinguished career, having served under both Democrats and Republicans in various roles, including at the State Department, Congress, the White House, and most recently at the Central Intelligence Agency. Biden commends her for taking on sensitive and difficult assignments and consistently delivering results. He is proud of Haines and pleased that she will be returning to the White House in her new role. Additionally, Biden congratulates Tony Blinken on his confirmation as Deputy Secretary of State and looks forward to continuing their partnership.